Introduction

I.O.I (acronym for 'Ideal Of Idol') was an eleven-member project girl group under YMC Entertainment and CJ E&M Music. They were formed through MNET's survival show Produce 101 and debuted on May 4, 2016, with the mini album "Chrysalis". The group promoted for less than a year before disbanding on January 29, 2017.

In November 2015, MNET announced their new survival show, called Produce 101, that would bring together 101 trainees from 46 entertainment companies to form a unit girl group with 11 members chosen by the viewers. The survival show premiered on January 21, 2016, and the live finale was broadcast on April 1, 2016, were the 11 winners: Jeon Somi, Kim Sejeong, Choi Yoojung, Kim Chungha, Kim Sohye, Zhou Jieqieong, Jung Chaeyeon, Kim Doyeon, Kang Mina, Lim Nayoung, and Yoo Yeonjung, became a girl group named I.O.I.

Prior to their participation in Produce 101, Kim Sejeong was already known for her participation in K-pop Star 2, Jung Chaeyeon for being a member of the girl group DIA, Choi Yoojung for appearing in the web drama "To Be Continued", and Jeon Somi for her participation in JYP Entertainment's survival show SIXTEEN.

Presumably, the day of the survival show's finale was supposed to also be I.O.I's debut with the song "Crush" and the beginning of their activities. However, MNET and YMC Entertainment decided to postpone it so they could prepare the group with their concept and a new song. Still, the song "Crush" was released on April 5, 2016, as a digital single, followed by its music video. I.O.I finally debuted a month after, on May 4, 2016, with the EP "Chrysalis" and the title track "Dream Girls".

After their debut, I.O.I. went on to release the single "Whatta Man (Good Man)", a remake of Salt-N-Pepa song of the same name, as a seven-member sub-unit (Kim Sejeong, Jung Chaeyeon, Yoo Yeonjung, and Kang Mina being the missing members) on August 8, 2016, and, as a full group again, the mini album "miss me?", with its well-known title track "Very Very Very" on October 17, 2016. Still today, this title song is considered an anthem and covered by many younger groups.

After the release of "DOWNPOUR", the group's disbandment song, on January 18, 2017, they held a concert titled "Time Slip – I.O.I", from January 20 to 22, 2017, marking their last group activity on stage. I.O.I officially disbanded at the end of January 2017 and each members returned to their respective agencies.

The group was planning to have a reunion in December 2019 with nine members under Studio Blu but, due to Yoo Yeonjung and Jeon Somi being unable to participate, the reunion was virtually cancelled. However, I.O.I. did have a reunion, although not a comeback, on May 4, 2021, on the 5th anniversary of their debut. The group, except Kang Mina, which couldn't be there due to her schedule, held a reunion livestream. Despite being unable to be physically present, Zhou Jieqiong still managed to join the live stream via video calling.
